<br>
Other than getting dual wield and getting pretty much all their combat skills earlier, I can't really see an advantage warriors have over SKs.  There must be less obvious things like skill caps or exp penalties or something...right?<br>
<br>
Ok...lemme explain.  I played a barbarian warrior to 30.  Started out crazy slow and is already totally dependant on a group.  If I can't get in a group where I'm at, I have to do one of two things...log and try later, or run around and try someplace else, which takes alot of time usually.<br>
<br>
Now, I'm starting to play an Erudite SK.  Haven't grouped yet, but he's solo'd to 17 with no problems so far.  He has spells that make soloing much easier, he has very closely as many HP as my warrior did, and he can save his own butt when he pulls something he can't handle ALOT better than my warrior.<br>
<br>
I have heard many, many times that SK's make better tanks at the highest levels than warriors.  I've heard they can hold agro better and can take more of a beating because they have spells that help both.  And I'm seeing already with my own eyes that SK's can actually solo, something warriors have a hard time doing...<br>
<br>
So...what am I not getting?  Is dual wield THAT fun?<br>
<br>
