<br>
Basically, if you know the maximum DPS of the mob, and the HPs of the warrior, you can calculate the exact speed necessary for your complete heal chain.  For example, let's say you're fighting a mob that maxes out at 1000 damage per second, and you have a warrior with 6500 HPs.  When that warrior engages his /defensive disc, he takes I believe 40% less damage for 3 minutes.  Now the mob is doing 600 damage per second.  Thus, at worst case, the warrior needs a complete heal once every 10 seconds or so.<br>
<br>
The hitpoints of a warrior become much higher, comparitively, above 50.  Check magelo to see the actual hitpoint calculation, and you'll see how much a warrior outdistances SKs and Paladins at high level for raw number of hitpoints.  Add the bonus from /defensive, and the warrior becomes the best tank when you absolutely need someone who won't go down fast.<br>
<br>
And that is the point of warrior.<br>
<br>
